%N A396909 Numbers that are the sum of two nonzero generalized pentagonal numbers (A001318).
%H A396909 Thotsaphon Thongjunthug, <a href="/A396909/b396909.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
%H A396909 Thotsaphon Thongjunthug, <a href="/A396909/a396909.sce.txt">Scilab code</a>
%e A396909 Let P be the sequence of nonzero generalized pentagonal numbers (see A001318). Then we have
%e A396909 2 = 1+1 = P(1)+P(1),
%e A396909 3 = 1+2 = P(1)+P(2),
%e A396909 4 = 2+2 = P(2)+P(2),
%e A396909 6 = 1+5 = P(1)+P(3),
%e A396909 7 = 2+5 = P(2)+P(3),
%e A396909 8 = 1+7 = P(1)+P(4),
%e A396909 9 = 2+7 = P(2)+P(4),
%e A396909 10 = 5+5 = P(4)+P(4).
%Y A396909 Cf. A001318. Supersequence of A332987 and A332988.
%K A396909 nonn,new
%O A396909 1,1
